# v2 playbook (auto-generated from F-059-063 chunk-08)

slug: accessibility-audit-test-automation
title: "Accessibility audit + test automation"
version: "1.0.0"
status: draft
last_reviewed: 2026-05-20
maintainers:
  - "faion-network"
content_id: 03a0af1885c34d55

tier_min: solo
complexity: medium
context:
  - solo
  - team
persona_hints:
  - P5
  - P6
group: role-qa-engineer
persona: "QA engineer / test lead in an indie or small-team product context."

intent: |
  Move from the messy starting condition to the explicit done state for: Accessibility audit + test automation. Done when: WCAG 2.2 AA conformance baseline measured, automated a11y scans wired into CI for changed components, manual screen-reader + keyboard checks scheduled per release, an a11y backlog is prioritised by user-blocking severity, and a no-regression budget is enforced in PR review.

scope: |
  Done when: WCAG 2.2 AA conformance baseline measured, automated a11y scans wired into CI for changed components, manual screen-reader + keyboard checks scheduled per release, an a11y backlog is prioritised by user-blocking severity, and a no-regression budget is enforced in PR review.

summary: |
  Accessibility audit + test automation. Done when: WCAG 2.2 AA conformance baseline measured, automated a11y scans wired into CI for changed components, manual screen-reader + keyboard checks scheduled per release, an a11y backlog is prioritised by user-blocking severity, and a no-regression budget is enforced in PR review.

non_goals:
  - "Tooling holy wars — picking the stack is a side-effect, not the goal"
  - "Org-design / hiring changes outside the scope of this engagement"
  - "Speculative work without an acceptance criterion to test against"

prerequisites:
  - "Stakeholder + decision-maker named at kickoff"
  - "Access to the systems / dashboards / repos the playbook touches"
  - "Budget signed for the tooling + telemetry this playbook depends on"

success_criteria:
  - "Done-state achieved as described in the scope: Done when: WCAG 2."
  - "Decision doc signed: continue / iterate / kill, backed by evidence."
  - "Runbook + acceptance criteria in source control, handed to on-call / next owner."
  - "All must-fix issues from Harden / Pilot closed; nice-to-fix backlog ticketed."

methodology_refs:
  - pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/a11y-basics
  - pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/a11y-testing
  - pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/accessibility-first-design
  - pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/ada-title-ii-compliance-2026
  - pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/cognitive-inclusion-design
  - pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/regulatory-compliance-2026
  - pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/testing-with-assistive-technology
  - pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/wcag-22-compliance
  - pro/ux/ux-ui-designer/accessibility-evaluation
  - solo/dev/automation-tooling/playwright-automation
  - solo/dev/automation-tooling/testing-js-ts-frontend

stages:
  - name: "Audit"
    intent: "Get an honest map of where things stand today for: Accessibility audit + test automation."
    tasks:
      - "Inventory current state, owners, and recent incidents"
      - "Identify the top 3 risks that block the desired outcome"
      - "Surface unknowns and missing telemetry up front"
    methodologies:
      - slug: a11y-basics
        path: pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/a11y-basics
        required: true
        tier_gate: pro
    outputs:
      - "Written current-state map (1 page)"
      - "Top-3 risk list with owners"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance only if all top-3 risks have a named owner; otherwise re-scope.
  - name: "Plan"
    intent: "Convert audit findings into a defensible execution plan with explicit cuts."
    tasks:
      - "Define done-state acceptance criteria"
      - "Sequence the smallest set of changes that ship the outcome"
      - "Cut everything that does not block the done state"
    methodologies:
      - slug: a11y-testing
        path: pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/a11y-testing
        required: true
        tier_gate: pro
    outputs:
      - "1-page plan with sequenced steps"
      - "Non-goals list (what we are NOT doing)"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance if every plan item maps to an acceptance criterion; rewrite the plan otherwise.
  - name: "Build"
    intent: "Land the first vertical slice end-to-end in a real environment."
    tasks:
      - "Implement the slice behind a flag or in a sandbox"
      - "Wire telemetry from day one"
      - "Get a real human (not just CI) to use it"
    methodologies:
      - slug: accessibility-first-design
        path: pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/accessibility-first-design
        required: true
        tier_gate: pro
    outputs:
      - "Working slice in a non-prod environment"
      - "Telemetry dashboard for the slice"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance when the slice runs end-to-end with one real user; loop on Build otherwise.
  - name: "Harden"
    intent: "Find the failure modes before users do."
    tasks:
      - "Run failure-mode tests against the slice (load, edge cases, abuse)"
      - "Close every must-fix; ticket every nice-to-fix"
      - "Re-run telemetry to confirm no regression"
    methodologies:
      - slug: ada-title-ii-compliance-2026
        path: pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/ada-title-ii-compliance-2026
        required: true
        tier_gate: pro
    outputs:
      - "Failure-mode report + closure log"
      - "Ticketed nice-to-fix backlog"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance only with zero open must-fixes; otherwise stay in Harden.
  - name: "Pilot"
    intent: "Run with a controlled blast radius before broad rollout."
    tasks:
      - "Roll out to a controlled subset (canary, beta team, single client)"
      - "Measure against acceptance criteria with real traffic / real work"
      - "Capture rollback signal in writing"
    methodologies:
      - slug: cognitive-inclusion-design
        path: pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/cognitive-inclusion-design
        required: true
        tier_gate: pro
    outputs:
      - "Pilot metrics vs. acceptance criteria"
      - "Rollback decision criteria in writing"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance if pilot meets all acceptance criteria; pause for fix or revert otherwise.
  - name: "Rollout"
    intent: "Move from pilot to general availability with confidence."
    tasks:
      - "Stage the rollout in defined cohorts / regions / risk bands"
      - "Hold each stage open until telemetry is clean"
      - "Communicate state to stakeholders at each step"
    methodologies:
      - slug: regulatory-compliance-2026
        path: pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/regulatory-compliance-2026
        required: true
        tier_gate: pro
    outputs:
      - "Rollout log (cohort-by-cohort)"
      - "Stakeholder update record"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance to the next cohort only after the previous is stable for the agreed window.
  - name: "Operate"
    intent: "Hand off as a steady-state operation, not a hero ticket."
    tasks:
      - "Document the runbook for on-call"
      - "Define the SLO + alert + escalation chain"
      - "Schedule the next review cycle"
    methodologies:
      - slug: testing-with-assistive-technology
        path: pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/testing-with-assistive-technology
        required: true
        tier_gate: pro
      - slug: wcag-22-compliance
        path: pro/ux/accessibility-specialist/wcag-22-compliance
        required: true
        tier_gate: pro
      - slug: accessibility-evaluation
        path: pro/ux/ux-ui-designer/accessibility-evaluation
        required: true
        tier_gate: pro
      - slug: playwright-automation
        path: solo/dev/automation-tooling/playwright-automation
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
      - slug: testing-js-ts-frontend
        path: solo/dev/automation-tooling/testing-js-ts-frontend
        required: true
        tier_gate: solo
    outputs:
      - "Runbook + on-call notes"
      - "SLO + alert config in source control"
    decision_gate: |
      Advance when on-call can resolve the top-3 likely incidents without the original author.

token_budget_estimate: 12000

